#3302
Choosing Feats~
   First you must choose your class.  You simply need to type @Ygain
@Y<classname>@n to gain a level in whatever class you qualify for.  For
information on what classes are avaialble see @Yhelp @Yclasses@n or to get help
on a specific class type @Yhelp @Yclass @Y<classname>@n.  @w The next thing you
must do is choose feats and to see what is available and see what you already
have.  To see what you already have type '@Yfeats @Yknown@n'.  To see what you
qualify for to choose type '@Yfeats @Yavailable@n'.  In both lists you will see
the names of various feats.  For help on a specific feat the help command is
generally @Yhelp @Yfeat @Y<name @Yof @Yfeat>@n for example 'help feat
toughness'.  In the event that there is no or insufficient help on a feat feel
free to look the feat up on http://d20srd.  Org/.  Once you have decided to
choose a feat type @Ylearn @Y<featname>@n for example 'learn toughness'.  If you
want to learn a feat with a specific subset, you need to seperate the general
feat name and the specific subset you wish to specialize in with a colon and no
spaces.  For example, skill focus can be specialized in the tumble skill and the
syntax would be: 'learn skill focus:tumble'.  Once you have learned all your
feats here at the trainer go north to learn about raising skills.  @n
