#3312
Combat Basics~
   &w Combat here is much like combat on pretty much any MUD, with a few small
differences.  First the combat pulses (or ticks) are about twice as long here as
on other muds.  The reason is to allow for more strategy in combat, through the
various use of skills, spells, and combat options.  We have tried to keep things
quick enough that combat is not tedious in situations where strategy is not
really necessary.  There are some basic combat commands that are available to
everyone, such as trip, feint, and so on.  Go west to read up on those.  To the
east is a description on the formation system, and an exlanation on how it works
to create an enhanced strategic combat experience that can make the most of the
DnD3.5 rules.  Also east is information on the hate system which will help
to teach you about how the game decides who gets aggro and how to control
it.  Go north to learn about deities and religion.
