#3314
Trip~
   &w The trip skill is actually a combat ability option that is available to
everyone.  In order to use this ability you must be fighting in the first row,
formation slows 1-3.  When you initiate a trip you are allowed one trip attempt
per normal attack that you have (not including other abilities or feats that
give extra attacks or extra attacks from wielding multiple weapons).  If you
have the improved trip feat you get one extra trip attempt.  Your trip attempts
are attack rolls made against the opponent's armor class without including their
actual worn armor or shield bonus.  If successful an opposed ability score check
is made involved strength and dexterity.  The larger opponent generally has an
advantage here in making the trip, and creatures with more than two legs receive
a defensive bonus.  Dwarves, being very sturdy, also receive a bonus to their
resistance roll.  If the trip succeeds, the opponent is placed on their back,
and must spend an action standing up again.  Usually this will allow them to
still make a partial attack, though they will not be able to make a full attack
(a partial attack means at max they will only make one attack).  If the trip
fails the other character immediately gets a free trip attempt against the
character that tried to trip them.  The same rules apply here.  Monks are able
to use any remaining trip attempts that they have as normal attacks.  &n
