#3315
Feint~
   &w The feint skill is another combat ability option that is available to
anyone.  Feint is an opposed skill check between the attacker's bluff skill and
the defender's sense motive skill.  A successful feint will make the defender
flat footed, which may open them up to a single sneak attack.  Ranged attacks do
not require a character to be flat footed to qualify for a sneak attack in
melee, though the attacker must not have the defender's attention.  Unless the
character has the improved feint skill, their feint attempt qualifies as a
partial action, limiting them to a single attack that round.  With the improved
feint feat, a feint attempt is a free action, and costs no attacks.  Feint tends
to generate quite a bit of hate, so it should be used sparingly in some
situations.  &n
